Two held on immoral trafficking chargesThe Aluva police have arrested a lodge owner and a youth on charges of immoral trafficking.The arrested have been identified as Thrissur Aloor native Nithin (25), who came to the Geo Gardens lodge on Aluva ESI Road, and the lodge owner Aluva Chunamgamveli native Thomas (55). Thomas is alleged to have facilitated the activities while Nithin is a customer. The police are on search for a woman who arranged girls for the customers. She escaped from the scene as the police arrested the other two. The arrest was effected by a team led by Aluva Circle Inspector T.B. Vijayan.